# VLAN-Based Enterprise Network with OSPF, DHCP & Wireless WFH Access

## ğŸ“– Project Overview
This project demonstrates a real-world **enterprise network architecture** implemented using **Cisco Packet Tracer**. The network connects two geographically separated enterprise sites (**Delhi and Mumbai**) using a **WAN serial link** and integrates **VLAN segmentation, inter-VLAN routing, OSPF dynamic routing, DHCP services**, and a **SOHO home router with wireless access** to simulate a **Work From Home (WFH)** user.

---

## ğŸ—ï¸ Network Architecture

### ğŸ”¹ Delhi Enterprise Site
- VLAN 10 â†’ `192.168.0.0/24`
- VLAN 20 â†’ `172.16.0.0/24`
- Inter-VLAN routing using **Router-on-a-Stick**
- DHCP pools configured on Delhi router
- Trunk link between switch and router

### ğŸ”¹ WAN Connectivity
- Serial Point-to-Point WAN link
- Network: `10.0.0.0/30`
- Delhi Router: `10.0.0.1`
- Mumbai Router: `10.0.0.2`
- Dynamic routing using **OSPF (Single Area)**

### ğŸ”¹ Mumbai Enterprise Site
- Enterprise router running OSPF
- DHCP pool configured
- Interface connected to home router:
  - IP Address: `150.0.0.1`

### ğŸ”¹ Home Router (SOHO)
- WAN IP obtained dynamically via DHCP from Mumbai router
- NAT enabled
- Acts as gateway for wireless clients

### ğŸ”¹ Wireless Client
- Laptop connected via Wi-Fi to home router
- IP assigned automatically via DHCP
- Represents a remote Work From Home user

---

## ğŸ” Traffic Flow (End-to-End)
1. Wireless Laptop â†’ Home Router (Wi-Fi)
2. Home Router performs NAT
3. Home Router â†’ Mumbai Router (`150.0.0.1`)
4. Mumbai Router â†’ Delhi Router (OSPF over WAN)
5. Delhi Router â†’ VLAN 10 / VLAN 20 network

---

## âš™ï¸ Technologies & Protocols Used
- VLAN (802.1Q)
- Inter-VLAN Routing
- OSPF (Open Shortest Path First)
- DHCP Server & Client
- WAN Serial Communication
- NAT
- Wireless LAN
- IP Addressing & Subnetting
- Cisco Packet Tracer

